            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [It is a well known fact that the cinchona has been recommended to our tree-planters as a valuable and easily grown tree. Professor Hilgard of the State University has repeatedly urged it upon our ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.12.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [Eugene Hilgard]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found<seg style="color: #000000; ">. The text given here is from ‘<name key="Cinchona">Cinchona</name>
                     </seg> cultivation’, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Daily evening bulletin</seg> (San Francisco), 24 January 1880. December 1879 is the latest date on which M could have written, in order for his letter to reach <seg style="color: #000000; ">California</seg> by late January 1880.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the basis of the context, the correspondent is identified as Hilgard, but see M to G. Englemann, 4 December 1880 (in this edition as 80-12-04a), which might suggest that M's correspondence with Hilgard had not begun at this time.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text of this note is reprinted in 'American Agriculture', </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Leader </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">(Melbourne), 3 April 1880, p. 7.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[It is a well known fact that the cinchona has been recommended to our tree-planters as a valuable and easily grown tree. Professor Hilgard of the State University has repeatedly urged it upon our horticulturists. Letters received from Baron Von Mueller of Melbourne, and Professor Hill of the Brisbane Botanic Gardens, have stated that in their opinion California is well adapted to the cultivation of cinchona.]</p>
